Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.files

Class LogFilesBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.files.LogFilesBuilder
  • public class LogFilesBuilder
extends Object
    Transactional log files facade class builder. Depending from required abilities user can choose what kind of facade instance is required: from fully functional to simplified that can operate only based on available log files without accessing stores and other external components.
    Builder allow to configure any dependency explicitly and will use default value if that exist otherwise. More specific dependencies always take precedence over more generic.
    For example: provided rotation threshold will be used in precedence of value that can be specified in provided config.

    • Method Detail

      • builder

        public static LogFilesBuilder builder​(DatabaseLayout databaseLayout,
                                      FileSystemAbstraction fileSystem)
        Builder for fully functional transactional log files. Log files will be able to access store and external components information, perform rotations, etc.
        Parameters:
        databaseLayout - database directory
        fileSystem - log files filesystem

      • activeFilesBuilder

        public static LogFilesBuilder activeFilesBuilder​(DatabaseLayout databaseLayout,
                                                 FileSystemAbstraction fileSystem,
                                                 PageCache pageCache)
        Build log files that can access and operate only on active set of log files without ability to rotate and create any new one. Appending to current log file still possible. Store and external components access available in read only mode.
        Parameters:
        databaseLayout - store directory
        fileSystem - log file system
        pageCache - page cache for read only store info access

      • logFilesBasedOnlyBuilder

        public static LogFilesBuilder logFilesBasedOnlyBuilder​(Path logsDirectory,
                                                       FileSystemAbstraction fileSystem)
        Build log files that will be able to perform only operations on a log files directly. Any operation that will require access to a store or other parts of runtime will fail. Should be mainly used only for testing purposes or when only file based operations will be performed
        Parameters:
        logsDirectory - log files directory
        fileSystem - file system
